summary:
The Security Council, 
Recalling previous resolutions and Presidential Statements, 
Reaffirming commitment to Syria's sovereignty, independence, unity, and territorial integrity, 
Emphasizing 11.1 million people in Syria require humanitarian assistance, 

1. Calls for principled, sustained, and improved humanitarian assistance to Syria in 2020; 
2. Demands compliance with international law, including humanitarian and human rights law, and full implementation of relevant resolutions; 
3. Renews decisions in paragraphs 2 and 3 of resolution 2165 (2014) for six months, until 10 July 2020, excluding Al-Ramtha and Al Yarubiyah border crossings; 
4. Demands safe, unimpeded, and sustained access for humanitarian convoys; 
5. Reiterates the need for a political solution to the Syrian conflict and implementation of resolution 2254 (2015); 
6. Requests the Secretary-General to report on alternative modalities for the Al Yarubiyah border crossing by February 2020; 
7. Calls for improved monitoring of humanitarian deliveries and an independent review of United Nations humanitarian operations; 
8. Requests the Secretary-General to brief the Council monthly and provide reports every 60 days on implementation; 
9. Reaffirms it will take further measures under the Charter in the event of non-compliance; 
10. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
